markets.title: Will Trump make 5 trips to Mar-a-Lago as President in Nov 2025?
markets.rules_primary: If Trump makes exactly 5 trips to Mar-a-Lago in Nov 2025 as President, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: A single visit begins when the President arrives in Mar-a-Lago and ends when the President has returned to the White House. A visit need not end to be included – i.e. if Nov 2025 ends with the President still there, that visit counts for the purposes of the count. If the President is in Mar-a-Lago at the beginning of Nov 2025, that will count as a visit.

markets.title: Will the federal government shut down for more than 54 days?
markets.subtitle: days:: Past 10AM ET 11/24
markets.rules_primary: If the ongoing federal government shutdown (starting October 1) lasts for Above 54 days (through 10:00 AM ET November 24), then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: A shutdown is determined by notices on the U.S. Office of Personnel Management website indicating the federal government is at least partially shut down due to a lapse in appropriations. Days are counted based on notices checked at 10:00 AM ET each day. If there are multiple government shutdowns during the relevant period, this market only applies to the first shutdown, as the market will resolve after the end of the first shutdown. Notices of emergency furloughs or impacted government operations count toward the shutdown days. Office closures due to holidays or inclement weather do not count. If no shutdown occurs during the period, markets asking for counts above zero resolve to No, while markets asking for zero days resolve to Yes. Clarification (10/11/25): Days count toward the total when OPM's website indicates an ongoing shutdown due to lapsed appropriations, regardless of whether such days are also federal holidays. For example, if a shutdown notice remains on October 13, 2025 (Columbus Day), that day will count.

markets.rules_primary: If the ongoing federal government shutdown (starting October 1) lasts for above 4 days (through 10:00 AM ET October 5), then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: A shutdown is determined by notices on the U.S. Office of Personnel Management website indicating the federal government is at least partially shut down due to a lapse in appropriations. Days are counted based on notices checked at 10:00 AM ET each day. If there are multiple government shutdowns during the relevant period, this market only applies to the first shutdown, as the market will resolve after the end of the first shutdown. Notices of emergency furloughs or impacted government operations count toward the shutdown days. Office closures due to holidays or inclement weather do not count. If no shutdown occurs during the period, markets asking for counts above zero resolve to No, while markets asking for zero days resolve to Yes.

markets.rules_secondary: A clean continuing resolution is a funding measure that temporarily extends current government spending at the previous fiscal year’s levels for a specified period, without incorporating any additional policy provisions, earmarks, or modifications to agency operations.

markets.title: When will Trump announce a new trade deal?
markets.rules_primary: If the President announces a new trade deal before Nov 22, 2025, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary:
For the purposes of this Contract, an announcement must satisfy ALL of the following criteria: made through official channels including White House press conferences, official White House statements, presidential speeches, official presidential social media accounts, or official presidential appearances; explicitly describes the arrangement as a "trade deal," "trade agreement," "trade memorandum," "trade pact," or uses substantially similar language indicating a formal trade arrangement; and involves at least one foreign country, territory, or international trade bloc.

Preliminary agreements, frameworks, or agreements in principle do count as long as they are presented as a new trade-related agreement. It also includes modifications or re-negotiated versions of previous agreements. New arrangements include, but are not limited to: agreements with a country, territory, or trade bloc with which the United States does not currently have a comprehensive trade agreement; agreements that cover trade sectors, industries, or product categories not previously covered by existing U.S. trade agreements with the same partner(s); or an agreement that establishes fundamentally different trade mechanisms, dispute resolution procedures, or regulatory frameworks compared to existing agreements with the same partner(s). The following qualify as announcements that trigger the Payout Criterion: a new bilateral trade agreement between the U.S. and another country, a new multilateral trade agreement involving the U.S. and multiple countries, trade memoranda of understanding that establish new trade frameworks, sector-specific trade deals (e.g., agricultural, technology, energy trade agreements), and trade arrangements that are announced as "agreements in principle" or "framework agreements."

The following do NOT trigger the Payout Criterion: informal statements, leaks, or "sources say" reports without official presidential announcement; announcements of trade negotiations beginning, trade talks being scheduled, or intentions to pursue trade deals; tariff announcements, trade sanctions, or trade enforcement actions that do not establish new bilateral or multilateral trade frameworks; Congressional approval or ratification of previously announced deals; announcements of trade visits, delegations, or diplomatic meetings without announcing an actual deal; or announcements regarding domestic trade policy changes that do not involve foreign partners.

markets.title: Will the U.S. impose tariffs on any sector from Norway in Oct 2025-Oct 2025?
markets.rules_primary: If the President of the United States has imposed any new (or increased) tariffs in October 2025 on any sector of Norway, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: The tariffs must be imposed through executive actions including bills signed by the President or actions by the Department of Commerce. The tariffs must be in effect for at least some businesses during the specified period to qualify. Conditional tariffs (e.g., "Tariffs will be imposed if...") do not satisfy the criterion until they are actually imposed. The market resolves based on tariffs that are announced and take effect, not merely proposed or threatened. Increases to existing tariff rates count as new tariffs. Tariffs can be sector-specific or apply broadly. Trade blocs like the European Union can be specified as the country. "Any country" or "any sector" options resolve to Yes if tariffs are imposed on at least one country or sector respectively.

markets.title: House passes bill to release Epstein files this year?
markets.rules_primary: If a bill that mandates any part of the federal government release files related to Jeffrey Epstein has ||chamber_stage|| before Jan 1, 2026, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: The bill must pass the full chamber (not just committee) for House or Senate passage. For "become law" markets, the bill must be signed by the President or become law through veto override. Presidential pocket vetoes that expire resolve to No. Joint resolutions are treated as bills. Treaties require two-thirds Senate approval for passage. The market resolves based on the first occurrence of the specified milestone.

markets.title: Will Yoko Kamikawa become the next leader of Liberal Democratic Party (LDP) before Jan 1, 2026?
markets.rules_primary: If Yoko Kamikawa is announced as the first new non-interim leader of Liberal Democratic Party (LDP) before Jan 1, 2026, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: The market resolves when the first new non-interim leader is officially announced by the party or credible sources. The person need not have taken office before the deadline date, only be announced as the incoming leader. Interim or acting leaders do not qualify unless they are subsequently announced as the permanent leader. If multiple persons are simultaneously announced as co-leaders, the market resolves proportionally. Leadership contests that extend beyond the deadline date without an announcement resolve to No. The announcement must come from official party channels or be confirmed by multiple credible news sources.

markets.title: Will Sébastien Lecornu leave Prime Minister of France before Jan 1, 2027?
markets.rules_primary: If Sébastien Lecornu has either officially announced their intention to leave as Prime Minister of France or has actually left as Prime Minister of France before Jan 1, 2027, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: The market resolves to Yes upon either an official announcement of departure or actual departure from office. An announcement must be made by the person themselves, their authorized representative, or the governing body of the office and reported by at least one Source Agency. Announcements of leaving more than one year from the statement do not resolve the market to Yes. Leaving office includes resignation, termination, removal, impeachment and removal, recall, or term expiration without renewal. Temporary absences such as medical leave, suspension with possibility of return, or delegation of duties while retaining office do NOT qualify. Death does NOT satisfy the Payout Criterion. Forced departures satisfy the criterion even without prior announcement.

markets.title: Will Jay Jones drop out of the Virginia Attorney General race?
markets.rules_primary: If Jay Jones drops out of Virginia Attorney General election before Nov 4, 2025, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: "Dropped out" means the candidate announces they are ending, suspending, or withdrawing from their campaign, files official withdrawal paperwork, publicly states they are no longer seeking the office, or endorses another candidate while stating they are no longer running. Suspending a campaign is treated as dropping out unless the candidate explicitly states they remain in the race. Death or incapacitation resolves to No, not Yes. Losing a primary or election, failing to qualify for debates or ballots, or being eliminated through the normal election process does not constitute dropping out. Once someone drops out, the market resolves Yes even if they later re-enter the race.

markets.title: Will Greta Thunberg be arrested before Oct 1, 2025?
markets.rules_primary: If Greta Thunberg has been arrested before Oct 1, 2025, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: For purposes of this market, "arrested" means being taken into physical custody by law enforcement authorities (including federal, state, local, military, or international law enforcement), voluntarily surrendering to law enforcement authorities in response to an arrest warrant, or being formally booked or processed following detention. This includes being handcuffed and taken to a police station, surrendering at a police station or courthouse with an attorney, being arrested in any country, or being detained at an airport or border crossing and formally arrested. An arrest warrant being issued but not executed, brief detention without arrest, questioning without arrest, house arrest or electronic monitoring without physical custody, being named in an indictment without arrest, or protective custody that is not an arrest do not qualify. All times are evaluated in Eastern Time.

markets.title: Will more than 230 Representatives vote Yea on the next omnibus spending bill, minibus, or government-wide continuing resolution (CR)?
markets.rules_primary: If the number of Representatives voting Yea on the next omnibus spending bill, minibus, or government-wide continuing resolution (CR) before Jan 1, 2026 is above 230, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: The vote count refers to the first final vote on passage in the full chamber, not committee votes or procedural motions. If no vote occurs before the deadline, markets including zero resolve to Yes (e.g., "Below 50") and markets excluding zero resolve to No (e.g., "Between 50 and 64"). If the bill passes but vote count is unspecified, markets including the maximum chamber size (100 for Senate, 435 for House) resolve to Yes. Post-expiration requests to change votes are not considered for resolution.

markets.title: Will Ryan Walters leave Oklahoma Superintendent of Public Instruction before Oct 1, 2025?
markets.rules_primary: If Ryan Walters has either officially announced their intention to leave as Oklahoma Superintendent of Public Instruction or has actually left as Oklahoma Superintendent of Public Instruction before Oct 1, 2025, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: The market resolves to Yes upon either an official announcement of departure or actual departure from office. An announcement must be made by the person themselves, their authorized representative, or the governing body of the office and reported by at least one Source Agency. Announcements of leaving more than one year from the statement do not resolve the market to Yes. Leaving office includes resignation, termination, removal, impeachment and removal, recall, or term expiration without renewal. Temporary absences such as medical leave, suspension with possibility of return, or delegation of duties while retaining office do NOT qualify. Death does NOT satisfy the Payout Criterion. Forced departures satisfy the criterion even without prior announcement.

markets.title: Will the United States announce it has taken a stake in Lithium Americas before Jan 1, 2026?
markets.rules_primary: If the United States has agreed to or announced it has taken a stake in Lithium Americas before Jan 1, 2026, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: An agreement or announcement qualifies if it involves formal signing of treaties, parliamentary approval with binding effect, official ratification, formal commitment by the head of state/government with constitutional authority, official statements by authorized ministers, official press releases, formal declarations during government proceedings, or official statements to international bodies. Phased implementation announcements and multi-party agreements where the country is a signatory qualify. Preliminary discussions, conditional agreements contingent on circumstances, opposition party statements, leaked documents, think-tank recommendations, general aspirations without specific commitment, draft legislation without approval, and regional actions (unless specified) do NOT qualify. Retraction of previously announced commitments also does not satisfy the criterion.

markets.title: Will Department of Transportation (DOT) or the Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) announce that it is unable to provide air traffic control services at a named facility (‘ATC Zero’) due to controller staffing shortages in 2025?

markets.title: Will the President sign  Executive Orders between Nov 23, 2025 and Nov 29, 2025?
markets.rules_primary: If the President signs any Executive Orders during Nov 23, 2025 to Nov 29, 2025, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary:
An "Executive Order" is a numbered presidential directive that: is formally titled "Executive Order" followed by a number, is signed by the President, is published in the Federal Register, and has the force of law. All documents officially designated as "Executive Orders" with sequential numbering count, including Executive Orders that are later revoked or amended.

The signing date as recorded in the Federal Register determines which period an Executive Order belongs to. The time zone for date determination is ET. If an Executive Order is signed on the last day of the period, it counts if signed before 11:59:59 PM ET. The Federal Register is considered "unavailable" only if the website is non-functional or explicitly states that Executive Order data is incomplete for the period. Routine publication delays do not constitute unavailability.

If, for example, the period was "Jan 1, 2025 to Jan 7, 2025," and the Federal Register published a numbered Executive Order on Jan 10 with a Jan 7 signing date, this would qualify for the purposes of this market. The latest Expiration Date of the Contract shall be two weeks after the end of the period.

markets.rules_secondary: An Executive Order must be formally titled "Executive Order" followed by a number, signed by the President, and published in the Federal Register. markets.rules_secondary: A party is considered part of government if one or more of its representatives hold at least one ministerial or cabinet-level position in the new government. markets.title: Will the federal government shut down for fewer than 92 days?
markets.subtitle: days
markets.rules_primary: If the ongoing federal government shutdown (starting October 1) lasts for less than 92 days (ends before 10:00 AM ET January 1, 2026), then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: A shutdown is determined by notices on the U.S. Office of Personnel Management website indicating the federal government is at least partially shut down due to a lapse in appropriations. Days are counted based on notices checked at 10:00 AM ET each day. If there are multiple government shutdowns during the relevant period, this market only applies to the first shutdown, as the market will resolve after the end of the first shutdown. Notices of emergency furloughs or impacted government operations count toward the shutdown days. Office closures due to holidays or inclement weather do not count. If no shutdown occurs during the period, markets asking for counts above zero resolve to No, while markets asking for zero days resolve to Yes. Days count toward the total when OPM's website indicates an ongoing shutdown due to lapsed appropriations, regardless of whether such days are also federal holidays. For example, if a shutdown notice remains on October 13, 2025 (Columbus Day), that day will count.

markets.title: Nicolás Maduro out in November?
markets.rules_primary: If Nicolás Maduro has resigned or otherwise left as president of Venezuela before Dec 1, 2025, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: An announcement that Nicolás Maduro will leave the office within the next year is also encompassed by the Payout Criterion. If Nicolás Maduro leaves solely because they have died, the associated market will resolve and the Exchange will determine the payouts to the holders of long and short positions based upon the last traded price (prior to the death). If a last traded price is not available or is not logically consistent, or if the Exchange determines at its sole discretion that the last traded prices prior to death do not represent a fair settlement value, the Outcome Review Committee will be responsible for making a binding determination of fair allocation. For the avoidance of doubt, the Exchange will distribute $1.00 for each Contract.

markets.title: Will Israel extradite Tom Alexandrovich to the United States before Oct 1, 2025?
markets.rules_primary: If Israel completes the physical transfer of Tom Alexandrovich through formal extradition proceedings before Oct 1, 2025, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: Extradition requires the formal surrender of the person by a foreign jurisdiction pursuant to bilateral/multilateral treaties, formal extradition requests approved by competent authorities, MLATs, or other recognized international legal mechanisms. The physical custody transfer must be completed with documented arrival in the requesting country's territory. Provisional arrests, deportations, voluntary surrenders, prisoner exchanges, renditions without due process, temporary transfers for testimony, transfers to third countries, and failed attempts do not qualify. The person must be confirmed through official identification or biometric verification. If the person dies before extradition completion, the market resolves to last fair price.

markets.title: Will between 430 and 435 House vote Yea on a bill that mandates any part of the federal government release files related to Jeffrey Epstein?

markets.title: Will Curtis Sliwa drop out of the NYC Mayoral race?
markets.rules_primary: If Curtis Sliwa drops out of NYC Mayoral race before Nov 4, 2025, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary:
"Dropped out" means any of the following: the candidate announces they are ending, suspending, or withdrawing from their campaign; the candidate files official withdrawal paperwork with relevant election authorities; the candidate publicly states they are no longer seeking the office; the candidate endorses another candidate while stating they are no longer running; or the candidate is disqualified by election authorities or courts and does not appeal.

The following do NOT constitute dropping out: death or incapacitation, losing a primary or election, failing to qualify for debates or ballots, temporarily suspending campaign activities without withdrawing, being eliminated through the normal election process, or reducing campaign activities while remaining a candidate.

Key provisions include the following: Once someone drops out per above criteria, the market resolves "Yes" even if they later re-enter. "Suspending" a campaign is treated as dropping out unless the candidate explicitly states they remain a candidate. Withdrawing from the race counts even if the person remains on the ballot.

markets.title: Will Donald Trump be more than 15 minutes late to Diwali Celebration on October 21st?
markets.rules_primary: If Donald Trump is late to Diwali Celebration on October 21st by above 15 minutes before Oct 22, 2025, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary:
Lateness is measured as the difference between scheduled start time and actual start time, rounded to the nearest minute (5:30 rounds to 6, 5:15 rounds to 5). Actual start time is when the person first appears at their designated speaking position. If the person is early or exactly on time, all contracts resolve to No. If the person cancels or fails to appear, all contracts resolve to Yes. If the person appears at the venue but does not speak, the contract resolves to No. For the purpose of this market, rounding down to any of the strike times will not count as "above." For example, if Trump is 5:15 minutes late, the 'above 5 minutes' contract resolves to No. 

For the purpose of this market, words said on a hot mic will not count. If the event is streamed and televised by multiple broadcasters at different times, the official White House stream can be used to resolve this market. If the official White House stream begins verifiably later than the start of the event, timestamps from other source agencies may be used to resolve this market.

markets.title: Will Donald Trump be more than 15 minutes late to Oval Office announcement on October 16th?
markets.rules_primary: If Donald Trump is late to Oval Office announcement on October 16th by above 15 minutes before Oct 17, 2025, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: Lateness is measured as the difference between scheduled start time and actual arrival time, rounded to the nearest minute (5:30 rounds to 6, 5:15 rounds to 5). Scheduled start time is the last officially published time. Actual start time is when the person first appears at their designated speaking position. If the person is early or exactly on time, all contracts resolve to No except the 0-minute contract. If the event is delayed for reasons beyond the person's control, lateness is measured from when they reach their position. If the person cancels or fails to appear, all contracts resolve to Yes. If the person appears at the venue but doesn't take their position, the contract resolves to No. *For the purpose of this market, rounding down to any of the strike times will not count as "above." For example, if Trump is 5:15 minutes late, the 'above 5 minutes' contract resolves to No.*

markets.title: Will the U.S. impose tariffs on pharmaceuticals from any country in Sep 2025-Sep 2026?

markets.rules_secondary: The tariffs must be imposed through executive actions including bills signed by the President or actions by the Department of Commerce. The tariffs must be in effect for at least some businesses during the specified period to qualify. Conditional tariffs (e.g., "Tariffs will be imposed if...") do not satisfy the criterion until they are actually imposed. The market resolves based on tariffs that are announced and take effect, not merely proposed or threatened. Increases to existing tariff rates count as new tariffs. Tariffs can be sector-specific or apply broadly. Trade blocs like the European Union can be specified as the country. "Any country" or "any sector" options resolve to Yes if tariffs are imposed on at least one country or sector respectively.

markets.title: Will the bill to unseal Epstein records receive a veto-proof majority in the House?
markets.rules_primary: If the number of House voting Yea on a bill that mandates any part of the federal government release files related to Jeffrey Epstein before Jan 1, 2026 is at least ⅔ of the members present and voting, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: The vote count refers to the first final vote on passage in the full chamber, not committee votes or procedural motions. If no vote occurs before the deadline, markets including zero resolve to Yes (e.g., "Below 50") and markets excluding zero resolve to No (e.g., "Between 50 and 64"). If the bill passes but vote count is unspecified, markets including the maximum chamber size (100 for Senate, 435 for House) resolve to Yes. Post-expiration requests to change votes are not considered for resolution.

markets.title: Will Tim Walz run for a third term as governor of Minnesota?
markets.rules_primary: If Tim Walz has announced that they will run for Governor of Minnesota in 2026 before Jun 3, 2026, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: The person must publicly announce their campaign for it to be reported by a Source Agency. Merely filing campaign paperwork with the Federal Election Commission or similar entity is insufficient without a public announcement. The announcement must be for the specific office and election year listed. Exploratory committees or statements of interest without formal campaign announcements do not qualify. Running for a party's nomination to contest the office counts as running for that office. The announcement must come from the person themselves or their official campaign, not from speculation or third-party sources.

markets.title: Will Eric Adams drop out of the 2025 New York City mayoral election before Oct 15, 2025?
markets.rules_primary: If Eric Adams drops out of the 2025 New York City mayoral election before Oct 15, 2025, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: "Dropped out" means the candidate announces they are ending, suspending, or withdrawing from their campaign, files official withdrawal paperwork, publicly states they are no longer seeking the office, or endorses another candidate while stating they are no longer running. Suspending a campaign is treated as dropping out unless the candidate explicitly states they remain in the race. Death or incapacitation resolves to No, not Yes. Losing a primary or election, failing to qualify for debates or ballots, or being eliminated through the normal election process does not constitute dropping out. Once someone drops out, the market resolves Yes even if they later re-enter the race.

markets.title: Will Tim Kaine vote for the next omnibus spending bill, minibus, or government-wide continuing resolution (CR)?
markets.rules_primary: If Tim Kaine votes for the next omnibus spending bill, minibus, or government-wide continuing resolution (CR) in the Senate before Dec 1, 2026, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary:
For purposes of this Contract, this refers to a Yea vote on first final vote of the next omnibus spending bill, minibus, or government-wide continuing resolution (CR) (not a motion to proceed or motion to invoke cloture), unless otherwise specified, after Issuance and before Dec 1, 2026 in the relevant full chamber (that is, not a Committee vote, though not every member of the chamber needs to have participated in the vote).

Once the vote has been closed and the correct result of the vote has been announced, a request by Tim Kaine to add, remove, or alter a vote shall not be considered for purposes of resolving this market, regardless of any change to the official vote tally reported by the website Congress.gov or any other Congressional source.

markets.title: Filibuster weakened before 2026
markets.rules_primary: If the U.S. Senate lowers the threshold for the filibuster by December 31, 2025, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: If the U.S. Senate changes its rules or precedent to lower the threshold for cloture for any legislative action whose threshold for cloture at time of Issuance is three-fifths of all Senators duly chosen and sworn, then the market resolves to Yes. Changes to reconciliation rules are not included.

markets.title: Will any member of Trump's Cabinet leave before Oct 2025?
markets.rules_primary: If any member of Trump's Cabinet leaves their office, or announces they will leave their office, from Feb 28, 2025 to Oct 1, 2025, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary:
The member must have been confirmed or appointed to their position after the President to be inaugurated on January 20, 2025 has taken office.

For purposes of this Contract, the Cabinet includes the heads of the 15 government agencies in the Cabinet as of Issuance, as well the Administrator of the EPA, the President’s Chief of Staff, Director of National Intelligence, Director of OMB, Director of CIA, United States Trade Representative, Ambassador to the UN, Chair of the Council of Economic Advisers, Administrator of the SBA, and Director of OSTP. Acting roles are not included. Leaving office as a result of death is not encompassed by the Payout Criterion.

markets.title: Will SB 79 become law before Jan 1, 2026?
markets.rules_primary: If SB 79 becomes law in California before Jan 1, 2026, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: SB 79 is a California bill that legalizes higher-density housing near some transit hubs, among other housing-related provisions. For the purposes of this market, if it becomes law before 2026, then the market resolves to Yes. This can occur through a governor's signature, through a governor's approval without a signature, or through a legislative override of a governor's veto.

markets.title: Will Sergio Gor be confirmed as U.S. ambassador to India before Jan 1, 2026?
markets.rules_primary: If Sergio Gor is confirmed as U.S. ambassador to India before Jan 1, 2026, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: The nominee must be confirmed by the U.S. Senate for the specific position listed. Acting appointments without Senate confirmation do not satisfy the Payout Criterion. If a nomination is withdrawn before the deadline, that market immediately resolves to No. Recess appointments do not count as confirmation unless explicitly ratified by the Senate. The confirmation vote must be the final vote on the nomination, not procedural votes or cloture motions. If the nominee is confirmed to a different position than specified, the market resolves to No.

markets.title: Government shutdown in 2025?
markets.subtitle: In 2025
markets.rules_primary: If the government is shutdown at any 10:00 AM ET before Jan 1, 2026, then the market resolves to Yes.

markets.title: Will Karoline Leavitt be more than 15 minutes late to Press Briefing on December 1st?
markets.rules_primary: If Karoline Leavitt is late to Press Briefing on December 1st by above 15 minutes before Dec 2, 2025, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: Lateness is measured as the difference between scheduled start time and actual arrival time, rounded to the nearest minute (5:30 rounds to 6, 5:15 rounds to 5). Scheduled start time is the last officially published time. Actual start time is when the person first appears at their designated speaking position. If the person is early or exactly on time, all contracts resolve to No except the 0-minute contract. If the event is delayed for reasons beyond the person's control, lateness is measured from when they reach their position. If the person cancels or fails to appear, all contracts resolve to Yes. If the person appears at the venue but doesn't take their position, the contract resolves to No. *For the purpose of this market, rounding down to any of the strike times will not count as "above." For example, if Leavitt is 5:15 minutes late, the 'above 5 minutes' contract resolves to No.*

If the person is early or exactly on time, all contracts resolve to No except the 0-minute contract. If the person appears at the venue but doesn't take their position, the contract resolves to No. *For the purpose of this market, rounding down to any of the strike times will not count as "above." For example, if Leavitt is 5:15 minutes late, the 'above 5 minutes' contract resolves to No.*

markets.title: Will Republican provide the 218 signature on Massie discharge petition on Epstein files?
markets.rules_primary: If a Republican has signed Discharge Petition No. 9 for H.Res. 581 (Massie discharge petition on Epstein files) as the 218th signature before Jan 1, 2026, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: A signature occurs when the Member's name appears on the official list maintained by the Clerk of the U.S. House of Representatives. The signature must be recorded and published in accordance with House rules. If a Member signs and then withdraws their signature before or after the petition reaches 218 signatures, this still satisfies the signing requirement. Non-voting Delegates and the Resident Commissioner cannot sign discharge petitions. Party affiliation is determined at the time of signing. If a Member dies or resigns after signing, their signature remains valid unless removed by their successor. For ordinal signature markets (e.g., "Who will provide the 218th signature?"), the market resolves based on which party the Member providing that specific numbered signature belongs to.

markets.title: Will the deficit be smaller in 2025 than 2024?
markets.rules_primary: If the federal deficit is smaller in fiscal year 2025 than 2024, then the market resolves to Yes.

markets.title: Will any measure primarily about ending or limiting U.S. import tariffs on any country or group of countries passed the Senate before Dec 1, 2025?
markets.rules_primary: If any measure primarily about ending or limiting U.S. import tariffs on any country or group of countries has passed the Senate before Dec 1, 2025, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: The bill must pass the full chamber (not just committee) for House or Senate passage. For "become law" markets, the bill must be signed by the President or become law through veto override. Presidential pocket vetoes that expire resolve to No. Joint resolutions are treated as bills. Treaties require two-thirds Senate approval for passage. The market resolves based on the first occurrence of the specified milestone.

markets.title: Who will Pope Leo XIV meet with before 2026?
markets.rules_primary: If Pope Leo XIV meets Recep Tayyip Erdoğan before Jan 1, 2026, then the market resolves to Yes.

markets.title: Will anyone dissent at the next Fed meeting?
markets.rules_primary: If there is a dissenting vote at the next Federal Reserve Open Market Committee monetary policy meeting, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: The next meeting is scheduled for Sep 17, 2025. NOTE: This market only encompasses a dissenting vote of the Fed Funds Rate decision.

markets.title: Will exactly 99 Senate vote Yea on a bill that mandates any part of the federal government release files related to Jeffrey Epstein?
markets.rules_primary: If the number of Senators voting Yea on a bill that mandates any part of the federal government release files related to Jeffrey Epstein before Jan 1, 2026 is exactly 99, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: The vote count refers to the first final vote on passage in the full chamber, not committee votes or procedural motions. If no vote occurs before the deadline, markets including zero resolve to Yes (e.g., "Below 50") and markets excluding zero resolve to No (e.g., "Between 50 and 64"). If the bill passes but vote count is unspecified, markets including the maximum chamber size (100 for Senate, 435 for House) resolve to Yes. Post-expiration requests to change votes are not considered for resolution.

markets.title: Will at least 3 of Trump's Cabinet nominees fail?
markets.rules_primary: If at least 3 of Trump's Cabinet nominees fail because they are withdrawn or fail Senate votes, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary:
For purposes of this Contract, “fail” means that the individuals either withdraw from consideration, have their nomination  withdrawn, or are not confirmed after a vote by the United States Senate with no further votes planned.  All three individuals do not need to fail in the same manner to satisfy the Payout Criterion. For purposes of this Contract, “Cabinet-level positions” includes the heads of the 15 government agencies in the Cabinet as well the Administrator of the EPA, Director of National Intelligence, Director of OMB, Director of CIA, United States Trade Representative, Ambassador to the UN, Chair of the Council of Economic Advisers, Administrator of the SBA, and Director of OSTP. For purposes of this Contract, a nomination occurs as soon as the President or President-elect announces their intent to nominate someone for a position. 

Multiple nominations for a single position are included; for example, if the President nominates three different persons for Attorney General and they all fail, that will be included within the Payout Criterion.
One nomination has already failed, that of former Congressman Matt Gaetz for Attorney General. This failure will count as one of the three necessary to satisfy the Payout Criterion.

markets.title: Will the House vote on an omnibus spending bill, minibus, or government-wide continuing resolution (CR)?

markets.rules_secondary:
For the purposes of this market, votes can include roll call votes, recorded votes, yea-and-nay votes, electronic votes (in the House), and Division/standing votes. Votes on cloture, on motions to proceed, and on final passage of a bill or motion will resolve this market to Yes.

However, voice votes where individual member positions are not recorded, unanimous consent agreements, votes in committee, presiding officer determinations, passages without an actual vote, and votes on amendments to a bill or motion (unless the market specifically refers to the amendment) will not count.

The tariffs must be imposed through executive actions including bills signed by the President or actions by the Department of Commerce. The tariffs must be in effect for at least some businesses during the specified period to qualify. Conditional tariffs (e.g., "Tariffs will be imposed if...") do not satisfy the criterion until they are actually imposed. The market resolves based on tariffs that are announced and take effect, not merely proposed or threatened. Increases to existing tariff rates count as new tariffs. Tariffs can be sector-specific or apply broadly. Trade blocs like the European Union can be specified as the country. "Any country" or "any sector" options resolve to Yes if tariffs are imposed on at least one country or sector respectively.

Note: Trump's tariffs on medium and heavy-duty vehicles, parts, and buses (proclaimed Oct 17) do not count because qualifying executive actions must be taken after Issuance.

markets.rules_secondary: The tariffs must be in effect for at least some businesses. The tariffs must not be conditional on any action.

markets.title: Will a bill containing full-year appropriations for one or more of the twelve regular appropriations bills, whether as a single bill, minibus, or omnibus become law before Jan 1, 2026?
markets.rules_primary: If a bill containing full-year appropriations for one or more of the twelve regular appropriations bills, whether as a single bill, minibus, or omnibus has become law before Jan 1, 2026, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: The bill must pass the full chamber (not just committee) for House or Senate passage. For "become law" markets, the bill must be signed by the President or become law through veto override. Presidential pocket vetoes that expire resolve to No. Joint resolutions are treated as bills. Treaties require two-thirds Senate approval for passage. The market resolves based on the first occurrence of the specified milestone.

markets.title: Will any Senator vote Nay on a bill that mandates any part of the federal government release files related to Jeffrey Epstein?
markets.rules_primary: If the number of Senators voting Nay on a bill that mandates any part of the federal government release files related to Jeffrey Epstein before Jan 1, 2026 is above 0, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: The vote count refers to the first final vote on passage in the full chamber, not committee votes or procedural motions. If no vote occurs before the deadline, markets including zero resolve to Yes (e.g., "Below 50") and markets excluding zero resolve to No (e.g., "Between 50 and 64"). If the bill passes but vote count is unspecified, markets including the maximum chamber size (100 for Senate, 435 for House) resolve to Yes. Post-expiration requests to change votes are not considered for resolution.

markets.title: Who will be named in Epstein documents released in 2025?
markets.rules_primary: If Tom Hanks is named in any context in any documents held by the federal government directly regarding Jeffrey Epstein and/or his crimes released before Jan 1, 2026, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: The context in which the subject appears does not matter for resolution. The subject is considered to appear in the documents when either the exact term, phrase, or name specified appears in the content of the documents, or the subject is present by way of commonly used abbreviation, direct synonym, or unmistakable reference including in any official appendices, footnotes, or tables. The documents must be publicly released after Issuance and before the end date. The documents directly issued and officially published by the relevant institution or entity, leaks of the documents, and media coverage by Source Agencies count, unless otherwise specified by the Exchange. If the documents are revised after publication, all publicly released versions prior to Expiration will be used. If a correction or update nullifies the appearance of the subject, the market may still resolve to Yes based on original reporting. The release time of the documents is noted to be when the documents are made available to the public either directly or through third-party media reports. If a document is heavily redacted, only visible, legible, and unambiguous references count.

markets.rules_primary: If President of El Salvador is the first leader among the above to leave office, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: An announcement that a leader will leave their position is not sufficient to resolve the Payout Criterion; the individual must actually leave and no longer hold the title. If any leader leaves solely because they have died, then all markets will resolve and the Exchange will determine the payouts to the holders of long and short positions based upon the last traded price (prior to the death) or another fair price.
